Storage resources are assessed by identifying available devices with lsblk and mounted filesystems using df -h command. Disk usage is analyzed with du -sh, inode utilization is checked with df -i, and I/O performance is monitored using iostat. Storage health is evaluated through SMART data (if available) and write speed tests performed with dd command. A comprehensive Storage_Assessment_Report.txt is created using the vi editor with observations and improvement recommendations.
